  FORMULA: chi_per = (1/(p-1)) * sum_m (-1)^m beta_m
    Since chi = sum (-1)^m beta_m = p * chi_per (from THM-125 + decomposition)
    chi = chi^(0) + (p-1) * chi_per_k>=1
    chi_per = chi^(0) when all k>=1 contribute equally (which they do!)
    So chi_per IS chi^(k=1) = sum_m (-1)^m beta_m^(k=1)

DONE.
